This file is currently just an outline.




The Identity datatype:

  \NEW{Identity}{\idDisguise}{
    \s\MYname	{Disguise}
    \s\MYmods	{\rs\MYdesc	{obviously disguised person}
		\rs\MYnumber	{????}
		\badgetrue
		}
    }




Identity instances:

  \newid{<command>}{<mods>}
  <command>[<switches>]{<arg>}
  \identity[<number>]{<name>}{<mods>}




Ready-made instances:

  \realname{<name>}
  \real[<switches>]{<arg>}
  \nickname{<name>}
  \nick[<switches>]{<arg>}
  \maidenname{<name>}
  \maiden[<switches>]{<arg>}




Degnerate Uses of Identities:

  \extrabadge{<name>}{<number>}{<desc>}
  \same
  \boxlabel{<label>}




Examples:

  \s\MYids	{\nick[\badgetrue]{}}


  \NEW{Item}{\iMask}{
    \s\MYname	{nice mask}
    \s\MYids	{\idDisguise{}}
    }
